{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "b98396c1-da88-4989-9ba8-5e1d65ff8759",
		"name": "Backend API - Async Workers Project",
		"description": "## Backend API – Async Workers Project\n\nThis backend system demonstrates production-ready Node.js architecture with async job processing, structured logging, security hardening, and request tracing.\n\n### Architecture Highlights\n\n- Layered architecture: Controller → Service → Repository\n    \n- Environment-based bootstrapping (.env.local / .env.dev / .env.prod)\n    \n- Graceful startup & shutdown lifecycle\n    \n- Structured logging using Winston\n    \n- Request tracing using X-Request-ID\n    \n- Background job processing using BullMQ (Redis)\n    \n- Global error handling with unified error contract\n    \n- Security protections (Helmet, CORS, Rate limiting, Validation)\n    \n\n### Background Jobs\n\n- Account creation triggers async email job\n    \n- Job queue: BullMQ\n    \n- Retry + exponential backoff enabled\n    \n- Worker runs as separate process\n    \n- Logs grouped using correlation IDs\n    \n\n### Global Error Format\n\nAll APIs return consistent response structure:\n\nSuccess:\n\n```\n{  \"success\": true,  \"data\": {}}\n\n ```\n\nError:\n\n```\n{  \"success\": false,  \"message\": \"Error message\",  \"code\": \"ERROR_CODE\",  \"timestamp\": \"ISO_DATE\",  \"path\": \"/api/endpoint\"}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Observability\n\nEvery request:\n\n- Receives X-Request-ID\n    \n- Is logged with correlation ID\n    \n- Includes execution time\n    \n- Structured logs stored in /logs/app.log",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "52130024",
		"_collection_link": "https://jaskirank-hestabit-864224.postman.co/workspace/05597a77-7d56-4e12-898c-468108fbf6bb/collection/52130024-b98396c1-da88-4989-9ba8-5e1d65ff8759?action=share&source=collection_link&creator=52130024"
	},
